\f0\fs24 \cf0 # User Interface Specification Document for the User Management Screen\
\
## Introduction\
This document is for the User Management Screen of our application. It explains what we need, the parts of the user interface, how the page should work, and what happens when users interact with it. This document is for developers who will create this user interface.\
\
## Requirements\
1. **Add New User**: We should be able to add a new user with details like Username, Display Name, Phone, Email, User Roles, and whether the user is Enabled.\
2. **Edit Existing User**: We should be able to change the details of existing users.\
3. **View User List**: We should be able to see a list of current users and have options to enable or disable them.\
4. **Hide Disabled Users**: We should have an option to hide users who are disabled.\
\
## Interface Components\
\
### Add New User Button\
- **Label**: "+ New User"\
- **Action**: Opens a form to add a new user.\
- **Location**: Top left corner of the screen.\
\
### Hide Disabled Users Checkbox\
- **Label**: "Hide Disabled Users"\
- **Action**: Hides users who are disabled from the list.\
- **Location**: Next to the Add New User button.\
\
### User List\
- **Headers**: ID, Username, Email, Enabled Status\
- **Features**: Shows a list of users, with options to edit and delete each user.\
- **Location**: Left side of the screen.\
\
### User Edit Form\
- **Fields**:\
  - **Username**: Text box\
  - **Display Name**: Text box\
  - **Phone**: Text box\
  - **Email**: Text box\
  - **User Roles**: Dropdown menu\
  - **Enabled**: Checkbox\
- **Actions**: Save button to update user information.\
- **Location**: Right side of the screen.\
\
## Page Behavior\
\
### Page Load\
- By default, the user list shows all users (both enabled and disabled).\
- If the "Hide Disabled Users" checkbox is checked, only enabled users are shown.\
\
### Adding a New User\
- When the "+ New User" button is clicked, a blank form opens on the right side.\
- After filling in the details and clicking "Save," the new user is added to the list.\
\
### Editing a User\
- When a user in the list is clicked, the form on the right side opens with that user's details.\
- After making changes and clicking "Save," the information is updated.}